data.enText: not used in the progressive tenses
He was charged with possessing a shotgun without a licence.

data.chText: 这座画廊藏有那位画家的一些早期作品。
data.enText: The gallery possesses a number of the artist's early works.
to have a particular quality or feature

data.chText: 恐怕他没有什么幽默感。
data.enText: I'm afraid he doesn't possess a sense of humour.

before.enText: of a feeling, an emotion, etc.

data.enText: to have a powerful effect on sb and control the way that they think, behave, etc.

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

before.enText: used in negative sentences and questions

data.enText: to make sb do sth that seems strange or unreasonable

data.chText: 他着了什么魔竟说出这种话来？
data.enText: What possessed him to say such a thing?

ex.enText: He has a house in the country.
The bottle still has beer in it.
The masses have boundless creative power.

synonyms.bx: 又作 have got, 指拥有某物并可随时使用，作此义解时，通常用于口语；也指具有某种外表、特性、特征等或包括某物在内。

ex.enText: We all enjoy free medical care.

ex.chText: 那里的人们享有广泛的民主和自由。
ex.enText: The people there enjoy extensive democracy and freedom.

synonyms.bx: 通常指享有声誉、权利、利益等好的东西。

ex.chText: 他持有这家企业的大部分股份。
ex.enText: He held most of the shares in the business.

ex.chText: 最后一名拥有该称号的英国人是谁？
ex.enText: Who was the last Briton to hold the title?

ex.chText: 关于此事，他们依然持那种看法。
ex.enText: They still hold that view on the matter.

synonyms.bx: 指拥有某些财产或头衔，也可表示心中怀有某种看法。
指具有所有权，尤指因购买、接受赠予等而合法地拥有。

ex.chText: 罗丝是一个拥有非凡智慧的女人。
ex.enText: Rose is a woman who possesses rare intelligence.

ex.chText: 我们需要品质优秀的年轻人。
ex.enText: We need young people who possess good qualities.

ex.chText: 他私藏海洛因的罪名成立。
ex.enText: He was found guilty of possessing heroin.

synonyms.bx: 通常指拥有某种好的品质、能力等，也指持有某物。

example: He owns three houses in Florida
How many cars does she have?

tr: have as an attribute, knowledge, or skill
example: he possesses great knowledge about the Middle East

tr: enter into and control, as of emotions or ideas
example: What possessed you to buy this house?

value.def: If you possess something, you have it or own it.

example.ex: He was then arrested and charged with possessing an offensive weapon...
example.tran: 他随后被逮捕，并被控拥有攻击性武器。

example.ex: He is said to possess a fortune of more than two-and-a-half-thousand million dollars.
example.tran: 据说他拥有超出25亿美元的财富。

value.def: If someone or something possesses a particular quality, ability, or feature, they have it.

example.ex: ...individuals who are deemed to possess the qualities of sense, loyalty and discretion...
example.tran: 被认为具备了理性、忠诚和判断力的人

example.ex: This figure has long been held to possess miraculous power.
example.tran: 这个数字长时间以来都被认为拥有神奇的力量。

value.tran: 具备，具有（特定品质、才能等）

value.def: If a feeling or belief possesses you, it strongly influences your thinking or behaviour.

example.ex: Tsvetayeva was possessed by a frenzied urge to get out of Moscow.
example.tran: 茨维塔耶娃内心有一种想要离开莫斯科的狂热冲动。

value.def: If you ask what possessed someone to do something, you are emphasizing your great surprise that they have done something which you consider foolish or dangerous.

example.ex: What on earth had possessed her to agree to marry him?
example.tran: 究竟是什么让她同意嫁给他的？

value.tran: （表示惊讶）是什么驱使…（干…），是什么促使…（做…）
